comments.content:
The animate and queue functions need slightly more flexible annotations on their arguments.

.animate():
The easing argument can be dropped with the callback becoming the 3rd argument.
See the 2nd example under Basic usage: http://api.jquery.com/animate/

.queue();
The queue-name can be dropped with the queue becoming the 1st argument.
http://api.jquery.com/queue

Here's what I've changed them to. Somehow I can't create a diff because the file is marked as a binary file in the svn (application/javascript mime-type)..

/**
 * @param {Object.&lt;string,*&gt;} properties
 * @param {(string|number|Object.&lt;string,*&gt;)=} arg2
 * @param {(string|function())=} arg3
 * @param {function()=} complete
 * @return {jQuery}
 */
jQuery.prototype.animate = function(properties, arg2, arg3, complete) {};


/**
 * @param {(string|Array.&lt;function(this:jQuery)&gt;|function(function()))=} arg1
 * @param {(Array.&lt;function(this:jQuery)&gt;|function(function()))=} arg2
 * @return {(Array.&lt;Element&gt;|jQuery)}
 */
jQuery.prototype.queue = function(arg1, arg2) {};
